{
  "texts": [
    "Second, we only extracted the year of the event, not the precise date, and the year for \"recent\" events was replaced with the year current to the note.",
    "The effects of our analysis might be influenced by this factor.",
    "However, we think that our approach is still valid in determining the direction of impact and magnitude of life events.We also omitted some stressful life events found in Holmes and Rahe scale by focusing on events with the highest mean score of impact (M > 40), only adding a handful of other events with a lower impact score, such as death of a close friend or losing financial support.",
    "Holmes and Rahe scale lists this latter event as \"Major change in financial state, \" which can also include financial gains, which we did not consider in our study.",
    "However, we think that concentrating on the most impactful events is justifiable to make an LLM-based extraction more accurate.Because analyzed events are rare and underreported in health records, it was not feasible to perform an initial power analysis."
  ]
}